abstract: JUNCTION CITY, Ore., Sept. 9 (AP)--Brilliant putting gave Clifford Ann Creed her second straight subpar round today-- a 4-under-par 68--and a fivestroke lead after 36 of the 54 holes of the Pacific Ladies' Golf Classic.

abstract: GREENWICH, Conn., Sept. 7--Fourteen young women were presented tonight at the fourth annual Debutante Ball of the Junior League of Greenwich at Mr. and Mrs. Julius Manger's home here. Mrs. Thomas F. Hodgeman and Mrs. George Hardin Brown were chairman and vice chairman, respectively, for the event, a benefit for the league's Community Trust Fund.
